# vfs_basic: exercise the PR-6a ZVfs engine surface (register +
# walk + stat + path + pathfromprovider) against a real on-disk
# tree via FSProvider. `{ROOT}` is template-substituted to the
# tmp_path by the test runner before the binary is invoked.
#
# Coverage:
#   - register fs (root dentry 0, providerid 0 in ZVfs.providers)
#   - walk root -> a (directory dentry 1), then a -> b.txt (file 2)
#   - stat all three dentries (dir/dir/file)
#   - path 2 reconstructs the VFS-side path "/a/b.txt"
#   - pathfromprovider 2 returns the provider-side "mounted/a/b.txt"
#   - cache-hit re-walk of "a" returns dentry 1 (not a new id)
#   - walk root -> missing produces a notfound dentry 3
#   - stat on notfound returns notfound
#   - pathfromprovider on the root returns "mounted" (FSProvider's
#     stored parentpath)
vfs register fs {ROOT} mounted
vfs walk 0 a
vfs walk 1 b.txt
vfs stat 0
vfs stat 1
vfs stat 2
vfs path 2
vfs pathfromprovider 2
vfs walk 0 a
vfs walk 0 missing
vfs stat 3
vfs pathfromprovider 0
